WEBVTT

00:01.001 --> 00:02.252
Previously on Empire...

00:02.335 --> 00:03.586
What you and I once were
is done.

00:03.670 --> 00:06.798
We're gonna start
a new business relationship.

00:07.924 --> 00:08.925
It's Adderall.

00:09.009 --> 00:10.301
Can you just go
do your drugs at your desk

00:10.385 --> 00:11.845
-like a normal person?
-Okay.

00:11.928 --> 00:13.013
Do you have Adderall?

00:13.096 --> 00:14.681
-Paul Bennett?
-He's an ASA vote.

00:14.764 --> 00:16.141
You're gonna escort
his daughter Piper

00:16.224 --> 00:17.392
to Laviticus.

00:17.976 --> 00:19.060
Perfect.

00:19.144 --> 00:20.895
I'm doing the work
that you're too soft to do.

00:20.979 --> 00:22.605
It's my show now, Andre.

00:22.689 --> 00:24.691
Do you still not
understand that?

00:25.900 --> 00:27.110
What in the hell
is wrong with you?

00:27.193 --> 00:29.446
It's about my sister Carol.

00:32.741 --> 00:35.702
His face was just so evil.

00:36.411 --> 00:37.996
I mean,
all I could think was,

00:38.079 --> 00:39.914
"He's putting hands
on my sister,

00:39.998 --> 00:41.624
and he's gonna kill her."

00:41.708 --> 00:43.376
He was shouting at me.

00:43.460 --> 00:44.586
You Holloway sisters
got a lot of mouth on you.

00:44.669 --> 00:46.963
I just felt cold
all of a sudden.

00:47.464 --> 00:48.923
Ice cold.

00:49.007 --> 00:50.592
I wanted to turn away and run,

00:50.967 --> 00:52.469
but then he came at me.

00:54.012 --> 00:56.181
And I killed him, Lucious.

00:56.264 --> 01:00.226
And then I just stood there
in shock.

01:01.603 --> 01:04.856
I mean, shock,
because I couldn't believe

01:04.939 --> 01:06.357
what I had just done.

01:07.400 --> 01:09.861
Damn, I mean, why didn't
you ever tell me that?

01:09.944 --> 01:11.237
I was scared.

01:12.572 --> 01:14.949
I mean, what if the cops
found out?

01:15.033 --> 01:17.368
You know, I couldn't
have you involved.

01:17.452 --> 01:18.745
We'd just started
the music thing,

01:18.828 --> 01:19.913
and I didn't want
to let anything

01:19.996 --> 01:21.122
get in the way of that.

01:21.206 --> 01:22.749
No, no, no, no.

01:22.832 --> 01:26.461
Murder is a dirty
and ugly business,

01:27.504 --> 01:29.547
but sometimes it's necessary.

01:32.383 --> 01:33.468
I know.

01:34.719 --> 01:37.097
Okay, the--the thing
with Tracy,

01:37.180 --> 01:38.681
I know I didn't--
I didn't have a choice,

01:38.765 --> 01:41.726
but Durrell...

01:43.394 --> 01:44.938
probably had a choice.

01:46.689 --> 01:48.566
Doesn't sound like it to me.

01:50.735 --> 01:53.154
We lost Carol after that
to drugs.

01:53.238 --> 01:55.115
She still talks
about this man to this day

01:55.198 --> 01:56.908
like he's the love of her life.

01:59.327 --> 02:02.413
I thought I was saving her,
but did I?

02:03.164 --> 02:04.833
See, that's
that damn therapy, man.

02:04.916 --> 02:05.959
It's messing with your mind.

02:06.042 --> 02:09.504
No, no, no, no, Lucious,
therapy is working, okay?

02:10.046 --> 02:12.048
Because through therapy,
I've realized

02:12.132 --> 02:15.718
I don't want to live
in any more secrets or lies.

02:17.178 --> 02:18.763
I want to live a clean life,

02:19.681 --> 02:22.308
and whatever I did wrong,
I want to make right.

02:22.392 --> 02:25.812
But that's the point
of the community center, right?

02:25.895 --> 02:28.356
Exactly, but my therapist says

02:28.439 --> 02:30.608
that you're only as sick
as your secrets.

02:31.609 --> 02:33.111
This thing with Carol,

02:33.486 --> 02:35.363
how do I make it right?

02:35.446 --> 02:39.492
Look, all I know is you don't
go digging up bones, Cook.

02:40.702 --> 02:43.163
Something ugly
always comes up with it.

02:49.460 --> 02:52.005
♪ ♪

02:54.674 --> 02:55.717
I don't get it, okay?

02:55.800 --> 02:57.385
Julian seems like
a really nice guy.

02:57.468 --> 02:59.679
Why don't you want anyone
to know that he's your son?

02:59.762 --> 03:01.890
Because he doesn't know, Becky.

03:02.307 --> 03:03.933
He doesn't know any of it.

03:05.059 --> 03:06.102
Okay?

03:06.186 --> 03:09.105
He doesn't know that I was
in my senior year at Stanford.

03:09.814 --> 03:12.442
He doesn't know that I had
my whole future

03:12.525 --> 03:14.444
mapped out on index cards.

03:15.904 --> 03:17.614
He doesn't know that
when his father found out,

03:17.697 --> 03:19.574
he transferred
to another school,

03:19.657 --> 03:20.742
just like that.

03:20.950 --> 03:22.035
He ghosted us.

03:22.118 --> 03:23.369
Damn, that's cold.

03:23.828 --> 03:25.455
You see, I thought
I was a superwoman.

03:25.538 --> 03:27.165
I thought I could do anything,

03:27.248 --> 03:28.833
so I chose to have him anyway,

03:29.209 --> 03:31.878
but when reality hit,
I realized I wasn't ready.

03:31.961 --> 03:34.505
-So I-I called on my mom.
-Oh, okay.

03:34.589 --> 03:35.673
So your moms took him.
Well, that's actually--

03:35.757 --> 03:37.133
You've got
the graphic design rep

03:37.217 --> 03:38.384
waiting in the conference room.

03:38.468 --> 03:39.928
Okay, thank you.

03:44.307 --> 03:45.683
Are you gonna tell him?

03:45.767 --> 03:46.809
I want to.

03:47.685 --> 03:51.022
I want him to know that all
of this success was for him.

03:52.190 --> 03:53.691
But how am I supposed
to let him know

03:53.775 --> 03:56.694
that he's been lied to
his entire life?

03:57.487 --> 03:59.489
Well, it's better that
he hear it from you

03:59.572 --> 04:00.990
rather than myancestors.com.

04:01.074 --> 04:02.200
Get to your meeting.

04:02.283 --> 04:09.082
♪ ♪

04:09.165 --> 04:10.875
♪ You run a hole right
through my brain, yeah ♪

04:10.959 --> 04:13.461
Okay, you've piqued
my interest, Lucious.

04:13.544 --> 04:14.796
When would we go wide with her?

04:15.255 --> 04:17.799
Actually, Adele
is looking for someone

04:17.882 --> 04:19.884
to open up
for her arena tour,

04:19.968 --> 04:21.469
and I think that Yana would
be the perfect mixture--

04:21.552 --> 04:23.179
No, no, no, no.
Adele can wait.

04:23.513 --> 04:24.847
You have to understand,
Becky,

04:24.931 --> 04:29.560
I have a very precise and slow
roll-out plan for Yana.

04:30.019 --> 04:33.022
I want to give the world
just a taste of her,

04:33.106 --> 04:36.818
just enough to build this
insatiable craving

04:36.901 --> 04:38.778
for the very nature
of her warmth.

04:39.028 --> 04:40.571
It's all about timing, people.

04:41.239 --> 04:43.032
I mean, Yana's potential value

04:43.116 --> 04:45.660
in the marketplace
is boundless,

04:46.369 --> 04:48.705
and with the help of the right
people from this room,

04:48.788 --> 04:50.623
under my guidance,

04:50.707 --> 04:53.876
we can accelerate her
towards superstardom.

04:53.960 --> 04:57.046
Yana has the voice,
the composure,

04:57.130 --> 05:01.676
that makes her the perfect fit
for billboards, selling makeup.

05:01.759 --> 05:02.927
You're thinking she's a brand?

05:03.011 --> 05:04.554
You're damn right,
she's a brand.

05:04.637 --> 05:05.847
A lasting brand.

05:06.556 --> 05:08.391
I chucked my entire company

05:08.474 --> 05:11.561
so that I can grow
this one particular artist.

05:11.978 --> 05:13.646
Lucious,
you're staking your name

05:13.730 --> 05:15.189
and reputation on this girl?

05:19.152 --> 05:20.945
♪ ♪

05:21.029 --> 05:22.113
Absolutely.

05:23.323 --> 05:25.116
Who's in?

05:25.450 --> 05:28.161
♪ ♪

05:28.244 --> 05:29.579
That's my man.

05:29.996 --> 05:31.164
Can I get another?

05:31.622 --> 05:33.791
Yeah.

05:36.711 --> 05:38.296
Can we get everybody in here?

05:38.504 --> 05:39.589
That's what I'm talking about.

05:39.672 --> 05:42.342
Now we are in
the Yana business.

05:43.885 --> 05:44.969
Take it again, Treasure.

05:46.846 --> 05:49.766
Listen, Porsha,
I have sang this song, like,

05:49.849 --> 05:52.185
I don't know, 30 times
and if he doesn't like it,

05:52.268 --> 05:53.311
then I don't know what to do.

05:53.394 --> 05:54.729
I'll talk to him, okay?

05:54.812 --> 05:56.022
I just need you
to do your part.

05:56.105 --> 05:57.231
Throat is killing me.

05:57.315 --> 05:58.691
Stall.
Do stretches or something.

05:58.775 --> 06:00.693
- We can do breathing exercises.
- Okay.

06:01.611 --> 06:04.489
Andre, you've been
going at this for hours, okay?

06:04.572 --> 06:05.698
She's tired.

06:06.240 --> 06:07.492
I need a star.

06:07.950 --> 06:11.079
Treasure, you need
to make a big splash

06:11.162 --> 06:12.288
at this Music Weekly show.

06:12.372 --> 06:13.414
You understand me?

06:13.498 --> 06:15.500
I'm talking to you!
Do you understand me?

06:15.583 --> 06:16.626
Okay.

06:17.960 --> 06:18.961
Do it again.

06:20.963 --> 06:22.590
You know, showing some support

06:22.673 --> 06:24.342
is the best way to get more
from your artist.

06:24.425 --> 06:26.844
Their egos can be fragile,
and so can their voices.

06:26.928 --> 06:28.888
I can't use fragile.
I need amazing.

06:29.389 --> 06:30.598
Excuse me, Andre.

06:30.681 --> 06:31.808
So Kendra G. from E!

06:31.891 --> 06:33.351
is dying to get a peek
at rehearsal.

06:33.434 --> 06:35.311
No cameras,
just an exclusive.

06:35.395 --> 06:36.979
- Bring her in.
- Not today.

06:37.605 --> 06:38.731
Andre, are you serious
right now?

06:39.941 --> 06:41.651
This is amazing.

06:41.734 --> 06:43.861
Andre, thank you
for letting me come in.

06:43.945 --> 06:45.029
Absolutely.

06:45.113 --> 06:47.156
You understand I am so excited
about the lineup

06:47.240 --> 06:49.325
for the Music Weekly
spring break event.

06:49.409 --> 06:51.285
You can get a sneak peek
at Treasure right now.

06:51.369 --> 06:52.620
-She'll blow your mind.
-Yes!

06:52.703 --> 06:53.996
-Take a seat.
-Thank you.

06:54.080 --> 06:56.916
Treasure, take it from the top.

06:58.334 --> 06:59.419
You got this.

07:04.841 --> 07:06.676
- Ow!
- Treasure, you okay?

07:06.759 --> 07:07.844
-Ow!
-Are you okay?

07:07.927 --> 07:09.303
-Treasure--
-My throat!

07:10.930 --> 07:12.098
It's my throat.

07:12.181 --> 07:13.766
I know,
but don't say nothing.

07:13.850 --> 07:17.645
Wait, is that blood?

07:17.728 --> 07:19.730
Can I get a--
can I get a medic?

07:19.814 --> 07:21.607
- What is that?
- I need a medic!

07:21.691 --> 07:23.651
-Why don't you come with me?
-Is she okay?

07:23.734 --> 07:24.819
I'm sure she's--

07:24.902 --> 07:26.237
I told you it was too much,
Andre!

07:26.320 --> 07:28.698
Whatever this is, Porsha,
fix it.

07:29.157 --> 07:30.158
Quick.

07:33.619 --> 07:39.750
♪ ♪

07:44.380 --> 07:48.926
♪ Some people walk for miles
for 1,000 hours ♪

07:49.010 --> 07:51.888
♪ But never
are the lucky ones ♪

07:51.971 --> 07:53.431
I got to be honest.

07:53.514 --> 07:55.391
This sounds much more
like a hit single

07:55.475 --> 07:56.642
than it does a demo.

07:56.726 --> 07:58.895
I was thinking
the exact same thing.

07:58.978 --> 08:00.563
I just wish Lucious
was on board.

08:00.646 --> 08:03.524
He thinks I should have
a whole roster of bulletproof,

08:03.608 --> 08:06.736
surefire hits before
I even step out there.

08:06.819 --> 08:08.529
He's so overprotective,
you know?

08:08.613 --> 08:10.448
Mm, overprotective.

08:10.531 --> 08:11.949
That's one word for it, okay.

08:12.033 --> 08:13.743
Look, I worked
with that man--

08:13.826 --> 08:15.661
for that man for years,

08:15.745 --> 08:17.246
and he is a control freak, okay?

08:17.330 --> 08:19.290
Even though it works for him.

08:19.373 --> 08:21.584
♪ If you find
that special thing ♪

08:21.667 --> 08:24.962
- Hey, girl.
- Oh, uh, hi!

08:25.046 --> 08:26.547
Hey, Giselle said
you wanted to see me.

08:26.631 --> 08:27.715
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

08:27.798 --> 08:30.343
Um, how are rehearsals
for the Music Weekly show

08:30.426 --> 08:31.802
going down at Laviticus?

08:31.886 --> 08:33.679
Eh, it's a little weird
for me to be over there,

08:33.763 --> 08:34.847
but it's okay.

08:34.931 --> 08:36.265
It is a bit
of a sausage fest

08:36.349 --> 08:37.725
since Treasure's voice
gave out.

08:37.934 --> 08:39.018
- Did it?
- Yeah.

08:39.101 --> 08:41.270
Doctors told her
to stop singing, stop talking.

08:41.354 --> 08:43.064
- Did they?
- Mm-hmm.

08:43.147 --> 08:44.273
Are they replacing her?

08:44.357 --> 08:46.984
No idea, but I doubt
the promoters have time.

08:48.653 --> 08:50.321
Huh...

08:52.406 --> 08:53.533
Excuse me.
I need to take this.

08:53.616 --> 08:55.284
Oh, yeah.
Go ahead, go ahead, go ahead.

08:55.368 --> 08:57.036
You take that.

08:58.246 --> 08:59.830
I'll take this.

09:02.542 --> 09:04.210
♪ ♪

09:04.293 --> 09:06.003
Hey, are you ready to fly?

09:06.087 --> 09:08.506
I've never been more ready
in my entire life.

09:08.589 --> 09:09.799
Okay.

09:09.882 --> 09:11.259
And I don't like being
held back, either.

09:11.342 --> 09:14.595
Okay, well, uh,
no guarantees,

09:14.679 --> 09:16.305
-but, theoretically...
-Mm-hmm.

09:16.389 --> 09:20.810
If I could secure you a spot
on that Music Weekly bill,

09:20.893 --> 09:22.812
what would Lucious
think of that?

09:22.895 --> 09:25.439
If I cared, theoretically?

09:26.691 --> 09:27.817
Well, let's just say,
theoretically...

09:27.900 --> 09:28.985
Uh-huh.

09:29.068 --> 09:30.653
I don't like asking
for permission, Becky.

09:30.736 --> 09:33.239
Well, theoretically,
neither do I,

09:33.322 --> 09:35.116
'cause we're grown-ass women.

09:35.199 --> 09:36.742
-Period.
-Period, boo.

09:36.826 --> 09:39.036
Let's do what we want.

09:39.120 --> 09:41.497
Wait, hold on.
Let's turn that jam back up.

09:41.581 --> 09:43.833
♪ Once in a lifetime ♪

09:43.916 --> 09:47.003
♪ ♪

09:49.088 --> 09:50.798
Look what you've done.

09:50.881 --> 09:53.634
Empire can't afford
to lose Treasure.

09:53.718 --> 09:55.886
Not now.
Give it up, Kingsley.

09:55.970 --> 09:57.638
-Shut up.
-Give it up, Kingsley.

09:57.722 --> 09:59.557
I know how to run this company.

09:59.640 --> 10:01.058
-Come on, give it up.
-Better than you.

10:01.142 --> 10:03.394
Watch me.

10:06.480 --> 10:09.066
♪ ♪

10:09.150 --> 10:11.777
Andre, the doc says Treasure
gonna be out of commission

10:11.861 --> 10:12.945
four to six weeks.

10:13.029 --> 10:14.155
You got to be kidding me.

10:14.238 --> 10:15.865
I wish I was, boss,
and it could be longer.

10:15.948 --> 10:17.491
-She might need surgery.
-Damn it, Porsha.

10:17.575 --> 10:20.244
This is your job
to get the artist up to speed

10:20.328 --> 10:21.412
and keep them there.

10:21.495 --> 10:22.496
Your job to make sure

10:22.580 --> 10:24.081
they don't hurt themselves
in the process.

10:24.165 --> 10:26.334
You right, it is my job,
and you didn't let me do it.

10:30.463 --> 10:32.298
You're right.
I'm sorry.

10:32.632 --> 10:35.176
-So, Andre--
-Not now, Maya.

10:35.760 --> 10:38.512
Porsha, how would you
have handled Treasure?

10:39.430 --> 10:40.765
Treasure's a homegirl.

10:40.848 --> 10:42.141
You push her, she push back.

10:42.224 --> 10:44.060
So I would have played it
to her strengths.

10:44.143 --> 10:45.853
Make her feel confident.
Make her feel strong.

10:45.936 --> 10:48.522
Make her want to do more
while respecting her limits.

10:48.939 --> 10:50.566
That's what you were
trying to tell me?

10:50.650 --> 10:52.026
Pretty much.

10:56.113 --> 10:57.490
I underestimated you,

10:58.032 --> 11:00.951
usurped your authority,
and ignored your experience.

11:01.744 --> 11:03.245
I'm not doing that again.

11:04.455 --> 11:06.165
-You firing me?
-No, the opposite.

11:06.666 --> 11:08.709
Empire's lucky to have you,
Porsha.

11:08.793 --> 11:10.753
As of today,
your promotion

11:10.836 --> 11:12.963
and new title of head of A&R
are in place.

11:14.340 --> 11:17.009
- Congratulations.
- Thank you, Andre.

11:17.385 --> 11:19.178
I'll announce it at the next
team meeting, okay?

11:19.261 --> 11:21.472
-Keep me posted on Treasure.
-You got it, boss.

11:21.555 --> 11:24.058
Thank you.

11:24.308 --> 11:28.646
♪ ♪

11:28.729 --> 11:29.939
The thing
about the choreography

11:30.022 --> 11:31.107
is you want to keep
it really simple

11:31.190 --> 11:32.191
and really classy,
you know what I mean?

11:32.274 --> 11:33.818
'Cause if we don't--
oh, I got it.

11:33.901 --> 11:35.528
Hi, hi, hi.
Thank you.

11:35.611 --> 11:38.322
Let me sign that IOU.
Thank you so much.

11:38.406 --> 11:40.324
- Becky.
- Just have to--hey.

11:40.408 --> 11:42.201
What the hell is going on here?

11:42.284 --> 11:44.370
Your assistant tells me
that you're setting up

11:44.453 --> 11:47.540
Yana's stage concept
for the Music Weekly show.

11:48.249 --> 11:49.250
- She's not ready for that.
- Oh, no.

11:49.333 --> 11:50.501
I think it'd be
a really great way

11:50.584 --> 11:51.585
to get her ready
for bigger venues.

11:51.669 --> 11:54.046
No, no, no.
I completely disagree, Becky.

11:54.130 --> 11:55.631
Oh, no,
you don't have to agree.

11:55.715 --> 11:57.091
You know, Yana's contract
is with Bossy,

11:57.174 --> 11:58.259
and that's me.

11:59.218 --> 12:01.554
Hey, Lucious,
I want to do this.

12:01.637 --> 12:03.055
No, no, you don't understand,

12:03.139 --> 12:04.724
and I don't expect you
to understand.

12:04.807 --> 12:05.933
That's not your job.

12:06.308 --> 12:09.478
I mean, your job is to listen
to the 30 years' experience

12:09.562 --> 12:12.815
I have in this business
and to follow my advice.

12:12.898 --> 12:14.692
Ooh, like a good little girl,
huh?

12:16.610 --> 12:18.654
Please, give me a minute.

12:18.988 --> 12:20.573
You're good.
I'm good.

12:25.244 --> 12:28.080
Yana, that's my artist.

12:28.164 --> 12:29.915
And this is my label.

12:29.999 --> 12:31.333
Oh, you gonna play that game?

12:31.417 --> 12:32.710
Oh, I'm not playing any game.

12:32.793 --> 12:34.295
The thing is,
you spoke your piece,

12:34.378 --> 12:36.046
and I heard you;
I hope you felt heard.

12:36.130 --> 12:37.631
But at the end of the day,
you know,

12:37.715 --> 12:38.799
I work for the artist.

12:38.883 --> 12:40.426
The artist looked at me
in my face

12:40.509 --> 12:41.719
and told me that she was ready,
and you know what?

12:41.802 --> 12:42.803
I believe her.

12:42.887 --> 12:44.680
Wait, wait, wait--
did you stop

12:44.764 --> 12:46.932
and consider that maybe
she might be wrong?

12:47.016 --> 12:50.186
Did I stop to think that
maybe--you know what?

12:50.269 --> 12:51.645
I did.
I did.

12:51.729 --> 12:53.147
I stopped,
and I thought about it,

12:53.230 --> 12:55.191
and then I made a judgment call,
and you know what?

12:55.274 --> 12:57.067
That is called a boss move.

12:57.151 --> 12:59.153
And you know what?
You taught me that.

12:59.236 --> 13:01.238
No, I've got plans for Yana.

13:01.655 --> 13:03.866
It's thought out,
it is measured.

13:03.949 --> 13:06.827
So either you take her out
of that damn set, or I will.

13:06.911 --> 13:09.747
Oh, okay, so I don't
really appreciate that tone,

13:09.830 --> 13:11.707
because if you'll
just take a look around,

13:11.791 --> 13:13.626
you'll see that you're
in my office, okay?

13:13.709 --> 13:16.170
I don't dance for you.
This ain't Empire.

13:16.253 --> 13:18.756
This is Bossy,
and at Bossy,

13:18.839 --> 13:21.091
you work for me.

13:28.599 --> 13:31.018
Girl, what the hell
are you doing up there?

13:31.101 --> 13:32.353
Andre just text me and told me

13:32.436 --> 13:34.605
I'm supposed to be meeting
a potential artist here.

13:34.688 --> 13:37.024
Uh, I actually sent that text.

13:37.107 --> 13:38.526
Uh, ex-squeeze me?

13:38.609 --> 13:40.194
Just listen.

13:41.737 --> 13:43.322
- Maya, I don't have ti--
- Just--just listen.

13:43.405 --> 13:44.865
Please, just a second.

13:44.949 --> 13:46.700
Uh, you can, um--
thank you.

13:46.784 --> 13:48.160
♪ ♪

13:49.495 --> 13:50.955
♪ ♪

13:51.038 --> 13:54.875
♪ I got so caught up
in the "what ifs" ♪

13:54.959 --> 13:57.461
♪ That I'm stuck
with "what now" ♪

13:57.545 --> 14:00.798
♪ I lost all my patience ♪

14:00.881 --> 14:03.509
♪ Need to find it somehow ♪

14:03.592 --> 14:06.637
♪ Can you imagine ♪

14:06.720 --> 14:09.682
♪ What life could be ♪

14:09.765 --> 14:12.393
♪ If being honest ♪

14:12.476 --> 14:13.936
♪ Was easy? ♪

14:14.019 --> 14:16.313
♪ ♪

14:16.397 --> 14:18.858
♪ I just want to
be a superstar ♪

14:18.941 --> 14:21.861
♪ Fly around the world
and drive fancy cars ♪

14:21.944 --> 14:24.822
♪ Buy my mom a crib
'cause she my rock star ♪

14:24.905 --> 14:27.491
♪ Is that so wrong,
is that so wrong? ♪

14:27.575 --> 14:30.911
♪ I just want to write a song
like "Billie Jean" ♪

14:30.995 --> 14:33.706
♪ Hope when I die one day
that y'all would sing ♪

14:33.789 --> 14:36.375
♪ I just want to know
that y'all gonna miss me ♪

14:36.458 --> 14:39.420
♪ Is that so wrong,
is that so wrong? ♪

14:39.503 --> 14:41.338
♪ Oh, if-- ♪

14:44.466 --> 14:48.387
Uh, did I--did I overdo it?

14:49.138 --> 14:50.598
Uh...

14:50.681 --> 14:52.516
No, actually,
that was pretty good.

14:52.600 --> 14:54.393
-Really?
-Yeah, I'm impressed.

14:54.476 --> 14:56.437
Maya, you can really blow.

14:58.731 --> 15:01.609
But you have no idea
how this business work,

15:01.692 --> 15:03.277
and you can't
ambush me like this.

15:03.360 --> 15:05.946
I just got this job,
and if you were my first sign

15:06.030 --> 15:08.782
as A&R head,
how would that make me look?

15:08.866 --> 15:09.950
You haven't even earned it.

15:10.034 --> 15:12.411
Porsha, come on.

15:12.494 --> 15:13.579
You and I both know
I have kissed

15:13.662 --> 15:15.915
my fair share
of Lyon family ass

15:15.998 --> 15:17.833
and probably made coffee
for, like, half of them.

15:17.917 --> 15:19.209
And?

15:19.293 --> 15:21.795
Maya, I spent seven years
for this kind of power,

15:21.879 --> 15:23.255
influence, and respect.

15:23.339 --> 15:26.216
You hear me?
Seven years.

15:26.300 --> 15:27.468
And I'm not about
to be abusing it

15:27.551 --> 15:29.345
the way I seen people do it
in the past,

15:29.428 --> 15:31.347
hiring a weed man
and nepotism nonsense.

15:31.430 --> 15:33.098
- I'm not doing that.
- Wow.

15:35.601 --> 15:37.770
I'm the weed man now?

15:38.938 --> 15:40.564
Wow.

15:40.648 --> 15:43.275
♪ ♪

15:43.359 --> 15:45.110
Cool.
Thanks for nothing, Porsha.

15:45.194 --> 15:46.862
You're welcome.

15:46.946 --> 15:48.405
I don't know what you thought
you was doing

15:48.489 --> 15:50.449
with your little Diana Ross
dress on anyway.

15:50.532 --> 15:52.701
♪ ♪

15:52.785 --> 15:53.953
What you thought this was?

15:54.036 --> 15:56.455
♪ ♪

15:58.916 --> 16:00.960
Damn it.

16:01.043 --> 16:02.211
Hold on, sis.
Hold on.

16:02.294 --> 16:03.629
- Hey, hey, no, no, no.
- I'll help you.

16:03.712 --> 16:04.964
I got you, I got you,
I got you.

16:05.047 --> 16:07.049
Hey, you just got out
of the hospital.

16:07.132 --> 16:09.259
Look at you,
sounding like Mom.

16:10.678 --> 16:13.055
Here.
Sit down.

16:16.684 --> 16:17.935
Oh.

16:20.771 --> 16:22.314
I miss her, you know?

16:23.649 --> 16:26.485
Mom was always
so, like, colossal.

16:28.654 --> 16:31.156
Like a superhuman.

16:31.240 --> 16:33.409
Well, she scared the hell
out of me sometimes.

16:34.660 --> 16:37.830
There was this one time where
I cheated on a spelling test.

16:37.913 --> 16:42.209
Yes, and when she found out...

16:42.292 --> 16:46.630
She laid into me
about what cheaters are,

16:46.714 --> 16:48.507
where they come from...

16:48.590 --> 16:50.884
And the snake-filled
cave in hell...

16:50.968 --> 16:53.387
That are waiting
for all the cheaters.

16:53.470 --> 16:56.598
After that,
I never cheated again.

16:57.975 --> 17:01.103
And I vowed never
to get anything less than

17:01.186 --> 17:04.273
a perfect score
on everything I did.

17:07.359 --> 17:09.945
She always thought
you were so brilliant.

17:10.988 --> 17:13.866
No. I was...

17:13.949 --> 17:15.909
I was just scared.

17:17.661 --> 17:19.747
Hey, hey.

17:20.789 --> 17:22.583
I miss her too.

17:24.793 --> 17:26.879
Oh.

17:26.962 --> 17:30.549
It's gonna be okay.
It's gonna be okay, baby.

17:33.927 --> 17:35.262
Talk about is what it's like

17:35.345 --> 17:36.472
to work with family.

17:36.555 --> 17:38.849
Cookie, you have famously
worked with yours.

17:38.932 --> 17:40.601
What is it like
to manage your boys?

17:40.684 --> 17:42.811
- Well, you know...
- Hey.

17:42.895 --> 17:45.105
Cute.
What's going on?

17:45.189 --> 17:47.399
Nothing, Mom.
Just going back to school.

17:47.483 --> 17:49.777
What? Wait.

17:49.860 --> 17:51.820
But break isn't over
for another week.

17:51.904 --> 17:54.114
What's the rush?
Is this about some girl?

17:54.198 --> 17:57.493
Look, I just got to leave, okay?

17:57.576 --> 17:58.660
No, actually,
it's not okay,

17:58.744 --> 18:00.037
and what is up with that tone?

18:00.120 --> 18:01.955
You've been snippy all day.

18:07.294 --> 18:09.379
Ma'am, we need to speak
to Quincy Barrow.

18:09.463 --> 18:12.883
I'm Quincy.
What do you want?

18:14.051 --> 18:15.761
Ma'am, is there a place
we can sit down?

18:15.844 --> 18:18.388
No.
Tell us what you want.

18:18.472 --> 18:21.183
This girl,
Piper Bennett,

18:21.266 --> 18:23.060
was found overdosed
in the club the other night.

18:23.143 --> 18:24.686
She's in a coma.

18:24.770 --> 18:26.105
Photos and texts
from her cell phone

18:26.188 --> 18:27.397
indicate that she was with you.

18:27.481 --> 18:28.774
Yeah.

18:28.857 --> 18:29.942
I mean, I got her
into the club,

18:30.025 --> 18:31.151
but I didn't see her
after that.

18:31.235 --> 18:32.653
Come on, kid.
What really happened?

18:32.736 --> 18:34.655
- Did you give her the drugs?
- Okay, enough.

18:34.738 --> 18:35.739
Unless you have a warrant,

18:35.823 --> 18:37.574
it is time for you
to get off of my property.

18:37.658 --> 18:38.742
- No, ma'am--
- My son

18:38.826 --> 18:41.286
has no obligation
to answer anything.

18:41.370 --> 18:43.038
Okay?
We know our rights.

18:43.122 --> 18:44.706
Thank you very much.
Bye-bye.

18:47.793 --> 18:51.922
♪ ♪

18:52.005 --> 18:54.925
Carol, no, no, no.
No need to come up, girl.

18:55.008 --> 18:56.510
It's pouring down outside.
Stay down there.

18:56.593 --> 18:58.470
I'm on my way.
Yes.

18:58.554 --> 19:00.264
I'm on my way down.
I'm coming, I'm coming.

19:00.347 --> 19:03.725
Oh, and I got tickets for you
and Candace for Tea Talk.

19:03.809 --> 19:05.352
Girl, En Vogue.

19:05.435 --> 19:06.687
No, no, no, no, no.

19:06.770 --> 19:08.063
I'm coming down now.
I promise.

19:08.147 --> 19:09.815
Stay in the car.
It's too wet, girl.

19:09.898 --> 19:11.733
Bye.

19:12.860 --> 19:14.987
-I-I need to talk to you, Cook.
-Okay, okay.

19:16.572 --> 19:19.032
How many times we got to have
this conversation, huh?

19:19.116 --> 19:21.910
You cannot come up here
unannounced, Lucious.

19:21.994 --> 19:24.955
No, I need you to put
Becky's ass in check.

19:25.038 --> 19:27.541
Yana is not ready
for the Music Weekly show.

19:27.624 --> 19:29.001
That's not the right venue
for her.

19:29.084 --> 19:30.752
You debuted her
on late-night television.

19:30.836 --> 19:31.837
No, no, no, no.

19:31.920 --> 19:33.005
That's a completely
different audience.

19:33.088 --> 19:35.215
This one will eat
her ass alive.

19:35.299 --> 19:36.508
Okay, listen, Lucious,

19:36.592 --> 19:38.468
Carol and I have a meeting
at the community center.

19:38.552 --> 19:39.928
I really don't have time
for this.

19:40.012 --> 19:42.764
No, no, no, can you focus
for a minute, please?

19:42.848 --> 19:44.391
I know you got a lot going on

19:44.474 --> 19:46.268
trying to put
your past behind you,

19:46.351 --> 19:48.937
but right now I need you
focused on the present.

19:49.021 --> 19:51.356
-I trusted Yana with you.
-You what?

19:51.440 --> 19:52.983
Negro, please.

19:53.066 --> 19:54.193
Do you know what
this means to me?

19:54.276 --> 19:55.360
Ah.

19:55.444 --> 19:56.570
Do you have any idea?

19:56.653 --> 19:57.696
I mean, I'm not gonna have

19:57.779 --> 19:59.489
a whole lot more chances,
Cookie.

19:59.573 --> 20:01.742
I just need you
for five minutes, please,

20:01.825 --> 20:03.744
to put the community center
and the therapy,

20:03.827 --> 20:05.662
shooting Durrell,
all that stuff behind you.

20:05.746 --> 20:06.830
-Okay.
-I need your help, Cook.

20:06.914 --> 20:09.750
I don't know why
I confided in you.

20:09.833 --> 20:13.545
You know damn well
I did not mean to kill Durrell,

20:13.629 --> 20:16.340
but I will kill your ass
if you don't get out of my way.

20:20.177 --> 20:21.553
Hey, Carol.

20:21.637 --> 20:23.347
Lucious, leave,
please, now.

20:23.430 --> 20:25.140
You said you wanted
to tell her.

20:25.224 --> 20:26.934
Ain't no time
like the present.

20:27.017 --> 20:29.353
♪ ♪

20:29.436 --> 20:31.772
You?
You?

20:31.855 --> 20:33.398
You killed him?

20:33.482 --> 20:34.816
You killed Durrell?

20:34.900 --> 20:37.653
Carol, just come in.
Let me explain, okay?

20:37.736 --> 20:39.780
Please, just come in.

20:39.863 --> 20:42.074
Carol.
No, no, no.

20:42.157 --> 20:43.617
He was hurting you.

20:43.700 --> 20:45.160
I-I just went there

20:45.244 --> 20:48.372
to tell him to leave you alone,
I-I swear.

20:48.455 --> 20:52.292
All this time,
I thought it was gangs.

20:52.376 --> 20:55.671
Carol, I tried to protect you.
He was beating you.

20:55.754 --> 20:59.383
And the drugs, Carol.
There were so many drugs.

21:00.133 --> 21:01.802
I'm sorry.

21:02.261 --> 21:03.595
I'm so sorry.

21:04.513 --> 21:06.974
♪ ♪

21:07.057 --> 21:09.685
Carol, please,
just say something.

21:09.768 --> 21:10.978
♪ ♪

21:12.813 --> 21:15.023
I'm okay.
I just, um...

21:15.524 --> 21:17.526
Whew.
I need to think.

21:17.609 --> 21:19.778
Um, I-I need to go home.
That's what I need to do.

21:19.861 --> 21:21.321
I think I'm gonna go home.

21:22.072 --> 21:23.865
You go to the meeting
by yourself,

21:23.949 --> 21:27.786
and, um,
I-I'll see you later, okay?

21:27.869 --> 21:29.871
- Carol, please.
- I'm okay.

21:30.789 --> 21:32.249
I'm okay.

21:33.583 --> 21:34.584
Okay.

21:36.295 --> 21:37.379
I love y--

21:37.462 --> 21:40.882
♪ ♪

21:41.341 --> 21:42.634
I'm sorry.

21:42.718 --> 21:44.928
♪ ♪

21:45.012 --> 21:46.138
I love you.

21:46.221 --> 21:48.307
♪ ♪

21:48.390 --> 21:50.475
Carol, I said I love you,
Carol.

21:50.559 --> 21:52.853
Car--Car--

21:56.982 --> 21:58.275
Right this way.

22:03.947 --> 22:05.198
Have a seat, gentlemen.

22:05.991 --> 22:07.659
We'd like to see
the security tapes

22:07.743 --> 22:08.827
for your club
the other night.

22:10.620 --> 22:13.415
A girl O.D.'d there.
Tainted drugs.

22:14.041 --> 22:15.959
We want to see
what your cameras saw.

22:16.209 --> 22:18.170
You gentlemen do know
I'm the CEO,

22:18.253 --> 22:19.338
not the nightclub manager.

22:19.421 --> 22:20.547
Why are you bringing this
to me?

22:20.630 --> 22:22.758
The girl's dad thinks
you'd do him a favor

22:22.841 --> 22:25.427
and cut through any red tape,
get this info for us quickly.

22:25.510 --> 22:27.637
Paul Bennett.
He's on the voting board.

22:27.721 --> 22:29.139
He's on the ASA committee.

22:29.222 --> 22:31.016
He's a good man.

22:31.099 --> 22:32.100
And he's right.

22:32.184 --> 22:33.477
I would do anything
to help him.

22:36.563 --> 22:37.898
I can get you that tape
within an hour.

22:38.523 --> 22:40.317
Anything else I can do?

22:40.400 --> 22:42.444
Should I ask around,
see if anybody saw anything?

22:42.527 --> 22:44.363
That would be helpful.

22:44.446 --> 22:45.822
Excellent.

22:45.906 --> 22:48.825
♪ ♪

22:48.909 --> 22:50.369
- Have a good day.
- You do the same.

22:50.452 --> 22:54.039
♪ ♪

22:54.539 --> 22:57.167
Um, Andre, it's Teri
on the phone for you.

22:57.501 --> 22:59.127
- Not now.
- She says it's urgent.

22:59.211 --> 23:00.337
I said not now.

23:00.754 --> 23:02.047
Wait.

23:04.091 --> 23:06.218
You didn't happen to be
at Laviticus last night?

23:06.301 --> 23:07.886
Sure, why?

23:08.929 --> 23:10.013
Come in.

23:10.097 --> 23:16.395
♪ ♪

23:20.440 --> 23:21.691
♪ Just to feel the touch ♪

23:21.775 --> 23:24.403
♪ Love has the power
to stick to you ♪

23:24.486 --> 23:25.862
♪ Just like a stain ♪

23:25.946 --> 23:28.365
♪ And then you're never
the same ♪

23:28.448 --> 23:29.533
♪ Some people walk for miles ♪

23:29.616 --> 23:30.700
Find your light, Yana.

23:30.784 --> 23:33.412
♪ For 1,000 hours ♪

23:33.495 --> 23:35.580
♪ And never are
the lucky ones ♪

23:35.664 --> 23:37.916
Keep your line of sight
above the stage lights,

23:37.999 --> 23:40.043
otherwise they will blind you.

23:40.127 --> 23:41.336
♪ Right here... ♪

23:41.420 --> 23:43.004
Chin up.
Greet your audience.

23:43.088 --> 23:44.172
♪ For us, ah ♪

23:44.256 --> 23:46.174
No, no, get back
in your spotlight.

23:47.426 --> 23:49.136
♪ Once in a lifetime ♪

23:49.219 --> 23:50.679
There you go.

23:50.762 --> 23:52.305
♪ Feels so right ♪

23:52.389 --> 23:54.266
No, no, stay inside
your spotlight.

23:54.349 --> 23:56.768
You've got to remember
your boundaries

23:56.852 --> 23:58.979
because this stage
is a whole lot different

23:59.062 --> 24:00.522
from those little coffee shops.

24:00.605 --> 24:03.066
-♪ Once in a lifetime ♪
-Perfect, perfect.

24:03.150 --> 24:05.610
All right, we're gonna start it
one more time from the top.

24:05.694 --> 24:07.070
Yeah, okay, no, wait.

24:07.154 --> 24:08.822
Lucious, wait a second.
We don't even have--

24:08.905 --> 24:11.241
Wait, no, no, no, there's--
there is no "wait a second."

24:11.324 --> 24:12.451
Oh, God.

24:12.534 --> 24:15.912
You have got to be
absolutely flawless tonight.

24:15.996 --> 24:18.248
I've invested so much time
and money into you.

24:18.331 --> 24:20.917
-I cannot risk--
-Money and time, Lucious?

24:21.001 --> 24:22.627
Is that what I am to you?

24:25.005 --> 24:26.965
Can y'all give me, like,
a quick second, please?

24:27.048 --> 24:28.925
Thanks.

24:29.009 --> 24:30.635
You want to know
what you are to me?

24:31.386 --> 24:33.430
You're the face of my dream.

24:33.513 --> 24:34.598
Of course.

24:34.681 --> 24:37.726
No, but you've got to use
everything I've told you,

24:37.809 --> 24:39.186
I've taught you,
I've showed you,

24:39.269 --> 24:41.313
if you're gonna win over
a crowd like this tonight.

24:41.396 --> 24:44.524
Lucious, you are smothering me
with your fear

24:44.608 --> 24:47.235
and all of this
negative thinking.

24:47.319 --> 24:50.113
I am going to go
out there tonight,

24:50.197 --> 24:52.949
and I'm gonna make it mine,
not yours.

24:53.950 --> 24:55.494
Yana.

24:56.286 --> 24:57.621
Yana, get back here!

24:57.704 --> 25:00.332
Bravo, Lucious.

25:00.415 --> 25:02.334
I see you still have
your magic touch.

25:02.417 --> 25:03.668
Excuse me?

25:03.752 --> 25:05.003
You know,
you used to be more convincing

25:05.086 --> 25:07.464
at making your artists think
you were working for them,

25:07.547 --> 25:10.383
but the truth is, is we're all
just slaving away for you.

25:11.134 --> 25:13.386
Let me ask you something,
Melody.

25:13.470 --> 25:15.430
Where have you been
for the last 20 years?

25:15.514 --> 25:18.808
If I ever need to know
how to work a karaoke machine,

25:18.892 --> 25:20.060
I will ask for your advice.

25:20.143 --> 25:21.144
You got that?

25:22.729 --> 25:24.397
Good to see you, Lucious.

25:24.481 --> 25:26.608
DJ Quarry.

25:26.691 --> 25:29.361
You doing this venue tonight?

25:29.444 --> 25:30.820
Oh, man, you know it, man.

25:30.904 --> 25:31.947
I'm in my bag.

25:32.030 --> 25:33.949
Good, good.

25:34.032 --> 25:36.159
This is gonna be nice.

25:37.077 --> 25:40.163
Melody, you got a minute?

25:40.247 --> 25:42.499
Yeah.
Exactly one minute.

25:45.544 --> 25:49.339
♪ ♪

25:49.422 --> 25:52.300
So that's why you been
blowing up my phone?

25:52.384 --> 25:54.469
Come on, Melody.
I-I need this.

25:54.553 --> 25:57.514
The blog says
that we were a couple.

25:57.597 --> 25:59.766
A-a romantic couple.

25:59.849 --> 26:01.560
And we were.

26:01.643 --> 26:03.687
Melody, I'm married.

26:03.770 --> 26:05.272
Q, you were married then, too.

26:05.355 --> 26:07.732
But I have kids now.

26:07.816 --> 26:08.900
I--

26:10.819 --> 26:14.281
I will lose them and my wife

26:14.364 --> 26:15.699
if you say that's true.

26:15.782 --> 26:16.992
So what do you want me to do?

26:17.075 --> 26:19.160
You want me to sit back
and say, "Ooh, yummy.

26:19.244 --> 26:20.745
I wish it was true,
but it isn't"?

26:20.829 --> 26:22.622
I mean, if you could
do that for me.

26:23.623 --> 26:26.042
Look, I stopped lying
a long time ago.

26:26.126 --> 26:28.128
I'm not about to start now
for you.

26:30.338 --> 26:32.674
But I also don't need anybody
in my business, either,

26:32.757 --> 26:34.593
so if that blog comes to me,

26:34.676 --> 26:36.511
